Concord v0.4.0-alpha.1
Release status: Experimental

This version adds authenticated witness-ledger primitives. It is not a
production-readiness declaration.

Delivery semantics are durable at-least-once with completion tombstones.
Exactly-once external side effects require application-level idempotency keys
or a prepare-and-commit protocol.

The witness ledger authenticates observations but does not establish semantic
correctness, scorer independence, causal influence, or deployment isolation by
itself. Complete-suffix deletion is detected only when verification requires a
separately retained signed terminal anchor.
